                  </persName>
            . I was in Smithfield at the Lock and Key, 
               <persName id="t18061203-68-person683">
                  John 
                  Edwards
               <interp inst="t18061203-68-person683" type="surname" value="Edwards"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18061203-68-person683" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18061203-68-person683" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             asked him if he had a horse to sell, he said yes; he asked him what he wanted for it, he told him four guineas and a half, he said very well, he would give it him then; when he came into this public house he gave him this writing for four guineas and a half; Riley was sitting in the room, Edwards asked him to write the note, and he did.</p>
               <p>BOTH - <rs id="t18061203-68-verdict414" type="verdictDescription">
